From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 15:12:08 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] drm/meson: disable pipeline dither on MIPI DSI mode set

L_DITH_CNTL_DITH10_EN enables a 10-bit dither LFSR in the ENCL output
stage. On a panel fed from an 8-bit framebuffer the dither has nothing
to dither against and emits pseudo-random LSB noise that appears as
speckle on solid colours.

Write 0 to L_DITH_CNTL_ADDR in meson_venc_mipi_dsi_mode_set so the
dither stays off for DSI panels.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_venc.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_venc.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_venc.c
index 3bf0d6e4f..e4a00e394 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_venc.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_venc.c
@@ -1696,7 +1696,13 @@ void meson_venc_mipi_dsi_mode_set(struct meson_drm *priv,
 	writel_relaxed(0, priv->io_base + _REG(L_RGB_BASE_ADDR));
 	writel_relaxed(0x400, priv->io_base + _REG(L_RGB_COEFF_ADDR)); /* Magic value */
 
-	writel_relaxed(L_DITH_CNTL_DITH10_EN, priv->io_base + _REG(L_DITH_CNTL_ADDR));
+	/*
+	 * Disable pipeline dithering on the MIPI DSI path. Pipeline
+	 * dithering targets a 10-bit ENCL output; on a panel fed from an
+	 * 8-bit framebuffer it just adds pseudo-random LSB noise that
+	 * shows up as speckle on solid colours.
+	 */
+	writel_relaxed(0, priv->io_base + _REG(L_DITH_CNTL_ADDR));
 
 	/* DE signal for TTL */
 	writel_relaxed(havon_begin, priv->io_base + _REG(L_OEH_HS_ADDR));
